### Description

Currently, Angular's @for structural directive allows iterating over arrays in templates:
@for (user of users(); track user.id) {
  {{ user.name }} is {{ user.age }} years old
}

However, there's no support for inline object destructuring like:
@for ({ name, age, id } of users(); track id) {
  {{ name }} is {{ age }} years old
}

# Why it's Needed:
- Reduces repetitive code like user.name, user.age inside the loop
- Keeps templates cleaner and more declarative

