not sure if its actually a bug or if I am just doing something that I shouldn't be. I have a component that is intended to open a mat-menu when clicked. If i attach the directive to an element within the component like `[matMenuTriggerFor]='subMenu'` then it works no problem. If instead I register the directive as a HostDirective like so:

```
@Component({
  selector: 'app-dynamic-menu-item',
  templateUrl: './dynamic-menu-item.component.html',
  styleUrl: './dynamic-menu-item.component.scss',
  hostDirectives: [{
    directive: MatMenuTrigger,
    inputs: ['matMenuTriggerFor:subMenu']
  }]
})
